    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @clementvp,\n\nIf you want to do an extract of your full data to a CSV file, you should use our JavaScript client directly: https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-client-js\n\nOtherwise, you could also do you own hits widgets like so:\n\n``` js\nvar myHitsWidget = {\n  _container: $('#myHits'),\n  getConfiguration: function() {\n    return {\n      hitsPerPage: 500\n    }\n  },\n  init: function() {\n    // if you need some jQuery code here, do it\n  },\n  render: function(args) {\n    var out = '';\n    args.results.hits.forEach(function(hit) {\n      out += '...'; // do whatever you want here, any html structure\n    });\n    this._container.html(html);\n  }\n};\n\nsearch.addWidget(myHitsWidget);\n```\n",
